1 Call Libraries and Set Options

library(tidycensus) # get tidy data from the Census

library(tidyverse) # tidyverse including ggplot

options(tigris_use_cache = TRUE) # options

library(mapview) # interactive maps

https://walkerke.github.io/tidycensus/articles/basic-usage.html

3 Census API Key

You will need to request your own Census API Key at: https://api.census.gov/data/key_signup.html

census_api_key("...") # Census API key

4 Get Data

Washtenaw <- get_acs(state = "MI", # state
                     county = "Washtenaw", # county 
                     geography = "tract", # geography level
                     variables = "B19013_001", # indicator
                     geometry = TRUE) # ask for geometry

6 Make a Map

Washtenaw %>% # data
  ggplot(aes(fill=estimate)) + # ggplot
  geom_sf() + # geom for shapefiles
  labs(title = "Quick Map: Washtenaw County",
       subtitle = "Median Family Income") +
  scale_fill_viridis_c() # viridis colors

7 Interactive Version

mapview(Washtenaw, 
        zcol = "estimate", 
        legend = TRUE, 
        layer.name="Median Family Income",
        map.types = "Stamen.Toner")

8 Try Different Themes (ggthemes)

https://jrnold.github.io/ggthemes/

8.1 WSJ

library(ggthemes)

Washtenaw %>% # data
  ggplot(aes(fill=estimate)) + # ggplot
  geom_sf() + # geom for shapefiles
  labs(title = "Quick Map: Washtenaw County",
       subtitle = "Median Family Income") +
  theme_wsj() +
  theme(title = element_text(size = rel(.75)),
        axis.text = element_text(size = rel(.5)),
        legend.text = element_text(size = rel(.5)))

8.2 Economist

Washtenaw %>% # data
  ggplot(aes(fill=estimate)) + # ggplot
  geom_sf() + # geom for shapefiles
  labs(title = "Quick Map: Washtenaw County",
       subtitle = "Median Family Income") +
  theme_economist() +
  # scale_fill_economist() + # discrete scale
  # manual replication of economist colors
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "yellow", 
                      high = "yellow4") +
  theme(title = element_text(size = rel(.75)),
        axis.text = element_text(size = rel(.5)),
        legend.text = element_text(size = rel(.5)))

8.4 A “Video Game” Look With darkunica

library(ggthemes) 

Washtenaw %>% # data
  ggplot(aes(fill=estimate)) + # ggplot
  geom_sf(alpha=.75) + # geom for shapefiles
  labs(title = "Quick Map: Washtenaw County",
       subtitle = "Median Family Income") +
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "green",
                      high = "darkgreen") + 
  theme_hc(style = "darkunica") +
  theme(title = element_text(size = rel(.75),
                             color = "green"),
        axis.text = element_text(size = rel(.5),
                                 color = "green"),
        legend.text = element_text(size = rel(.5),
                                   color = "green"))
